      systemGsapRequired = {
        id: "composer.system.gsap-required",
        category: "rule",
        priority: 25,
        appliesTo: {
          stages: ["composer"],
          roles: ["system"],
          requiresFlags: ["forceAllGsap"]
        },
        body: [
          "## ANIMATION ENGINE (REQUIRED)",
          "",
          "You MUST use GSAP timelines for this scene's motion. The Remotion `interpolate()`",
          "and `spring()` helpers are forbidden for element animation in this mode \u2014 they",
          "produce visibly simpler motion than what we need.",
          "",
          "Required pattern (copy this shape, adapt the content):",
          "```tsx",
          "const frame = useCurrentFrame();",
          "const { fps } = useVideoConfig();",
          "const containerRef = useRef(null);",
          "const tlRef = useRef(null);",
          "",
          "useEffect(() => {",
          "  if (!containerRef.current) return;",
          "  const tl = gsap.timeline({ paused: true });",
          "  // Build your multi-element choreography here. Examples:",
          "  tl.from(containerRef.current.querySelector('.headline'), { y: 80, opacity: 0, duration: 0.7, ease: 'power3.out' });",
          "  tl.from(containerRef.current.querySelectorAll('.chip'), { scale: 0, opacity: 0, stagger: 0.06, ease: 'back.out(1.8)' }, '-=0.3');",
          "  tl.from(containerRef.current.querySelector('.subtitle'), { y: 40, opacity: 0, duration: 0.5 }, '-=0.2');",
          "  tlRef.current = tl;",
          "  return () => { tl.kill(); };",
          "}, []);",
          "",
          "useEffect(() => {",
          "  if (tlRef.current) tlRef.current.seek(frame / fps);",
          "}, [frame]);",
          "```",
          "",
          "Rules:",
          "- EVERY animated element must be driven by `gsap.timeline()` + `tl.seek(frame / fps)`.",
          "- Use at least 3 distinct `.from()` / `.to()` calls \u2014 a single one is not a timeline.",
          "- Use GSAP plugins aggressively when they fit: `SplitText` for per-char/word reveals,",
          "  `DrawSVGPlugin` for stroke-on diagrams, `MorphSVGPlugin` for shape transforms,",
          "  `MotionPathPlugin` for curved trajectories, `Physics2DPlugin` for gravity,",
          "  `ScrambleTextPlugin` for matrix/terminal effects.",
          "- Prefer `ease: 'power3.out'`, `'back.out(1.7)'`, `'elastic.out(1, 0.3)'`, `'expo.out'`",
          "  over linear or default easing.",
          "- Overlap entrances with negative relative offsets (`'-=0.3'`) so elements don't wait",
          "  for each other in a dead line.",
          "- `interpolate()` / `spring()` MAY still be used for camera-level transforms (a parent",
          "  `scale(...) rotate(...)` that wraps the whole scene) but NOT for element motion.",
          "",
          "## ABSOLUTE GSAP TARGETING RULE (READ TWICE \u2014 runtime crashes happen here)",
          "",
          "NEVER pass a bare selector string like `gsap.from('.headline', {...})` or",
          "`gsap.to('.chip', {...})`. Bare selectors search the ENTIRE document, but the document",
          "only contains your scene during render. If the className isn't currently mounted, GSAP",
          "throws `target null not found` and the animation silently breaks.",
          "",
          "ALWAYS scope to the container ref \u2014 every targeted element must be reachable through",
          "`containerRef.current.querySelector(...)` or `containerRef.current.querySelectorAll(...)`,",
          "OR be a direct ref. The pattern is non-negotiable:",
          "",
          "BAD (will crash with 'target null not found'):",
          "```tsx",
          "tl.from('.headline', { y: 50, opacity: 0 });           // DON'T",
          "tl.from('.chip', { scale: 0, stagger: 0.1 });          // DON'T",
          "gsap.set('.subtitle', { autoAlpha: 0 });               // DON'T",
          "```",
          "",
          "GOOD (always works):",
          "```tsx",
          "const headlineEl = containerRef.current.querySelector('.headline');",
          "const chipEls = containerRef.current.querySelectorAll('.chip');",
          "if (headlineEl) tl.from(headlineEl, { y: 50, opacity: 0 });",
          "if (chipEls.length) tl.from(chipEls, { scale: 0, stagger: 0.1 });",
          "```",
          "",
          "Even better: use `useRef` for the elements you'll animate:",
          "```tsx",
          "const headlineRef = useRef(null);",
          "const subtitleRef = useRef(null);",
          "// ...in JSX: <h1 ref={headlineRef}>...</h1>",
          "useEffect(() => {",
          "  if (!headlineRef.current) return;",
          "  tl.from(headlineRef.current, { y: 50, opacity: 0 });",
          "}, []);",
          "```",
          "",
          "For every className you reference in a `gsap.X(...)` call, that className MUST appear on",
          "a JSX element you render. If you write `gsap.from('.foo', ...)` you must also have",
          '`<div className="foo">` somewhere. Audit your code before submitting: every selector',
          "string in a gsap call \u2192 confirm there's a matching className in the JSX."
        ].join("\n")
      };
