      systemRuntimeSafety = {
        id: "composer.system.runtime-safety",
        category: "rule",
        priority: 28,
        appliesTo: { stages: ["composer"], roles: ["system"] },
        body: [
          "## RUNTIME SAFETY (READ \u2014 these are the top 4 reasons scenes get rejected)",
          "",
          "### 1. TDZ \u2014 GOLDEN RULE: DERIVED VALUES GO INSIDE THEIR LOOP",
          "",
          "This is the #1 reason scenes get rejected. The fix is ONE rule:",
          "",
          "**If a value depends on a loop variable (`i`, `index`, iteration), compute it**",
          "**INSIDE the loop/callback body. Never at module scope.**",
          "",
          "This rule alone eliminates every TDZ error we've seen. The pattern the AI keeps",
          "reaching for \u2014 define once at module scope, reference inside .map \u2014 is WRONG.",
          "",
          "```tsx",
          "// \u274C WRONG \u2014 `i` doesn't exist at module scope",
          "const angle = (i / count) * Math.PI * 2;",
          "const positions = Array.from({ length: count }, (_, i) => ({",
          "  x: Math.cos(angle) * radius  // `angle` was computed with NO i",
          "}));",
          "",
          "// \u2705 RIGHT \u2014 compute angle inside the callback where i exists",
          "const positions = Array.from({ length: count }, (_, i) => {",
          "  const angle = (i / count) * Math.PI * 2;",
          "  const x = Math.cos(angle) * radius;",
          "  return { x, y: Math.sin(angle) * radius };",
          "});",
          "```",
          "",
          "```tsx",
          "// \u274C WRONG \u2014 `easedDigit` uses `digitProgress` before .map declares it",
          "const easedDigit = digitProgress < 0.5 ? digitProgress * 2 : 1;",
          "const digits = nums.map((n, digitProgress) => easedDigit * n);",
          "",
          "// \u2705 RIGHT",
          "const digits = nums.map((n, digitProgress) => {",
          "  const easedDigit = digitProgress < 0.5 ? digitProgress * 2 : 1;",
          "  return easedDigit * n;",
          "});",
          "```",
          "",
          "**Secondary rule**: if value `B` depends on value `A` (no loop involved), declare `A`",
          "first, then `B`. Forward references throw `Cannot access X before initialization`:",
          "",
          "```tsx",
          "// \u274C WRONG",
          "const ghostGlitchSample = isGlitching ? freqA : freqB;",
          "const isGlitching = frame >= 95;  // declared LATER \u2192 crash",
          "",
          "// \u2705 RIGHT",
          "const isGlitching = frame >= 95;",
          "const ghostGlitchSample = isGlitching ? freqA : freqB;",
          "```",
          "",
          "Order of operations inside the component body, top to bottom:",
          "  1. `useCurrentFrame()`, `useVideoConfig()` hooks",
          "  2. `useRef(null)` declarations",
          "  3. `useState()` if any",
          "  4. Pure helper functions (arrow functions / constants not depending on loop vars)",
          "  5. `interpolate()`, `spring()` derived values (in dependency order)",
          "  6. Arrays/data (`const buckets = [...]`)",
          "  7. `.map()` / `Array.from()` \u2014 derive per-iteration values INSIDE the callback",
          "  8. `useEffect()` blocks",
          "  9. `return (...)` JSX",
          "",
          "Before you write any `.map(...)` or `Array.from(..., (_, i) => ...)`: ask yourself",
          "'does this iteration produce values I'll compute at module scope?' If yes \u2014 STOP \u2014",
          "move those computations INSIDE the callback.",
          "",
          "### 2. CLOSE EVERY TEMPLATE LITERAL",
          "Every backtick `` ` `` opens a template literal that MUST close with another backtick.",
          "Inside `${...}` interpolations, regular code rules apply (string quotes, brackets, etc.)",
          "and you can NOT have an unmatched `${` without its matching `}`. After the closing `}`",
          "of an interpolation you are STILL inside the template literal until you write the",
          "closing backtick. Common failures:",
          "",
          "BAD:",
          "```tsx",
          "transform: `rotate(${angle}deg)  // \u2190 missing closing backtick before ,",
          "opacity: 0.8,",
          "```",
          "",
          "GOOD:",
          "```tsx",
          "transform: `rotate(${angle}deg)`,  // backtick closed before comma",
          "opacity: 0.8,",
          "```",
          "",
          "For multi-line template literals (e.g. CSS gradients), the backticks still must balance:",
          "```tsx",
          "background: `radial-gradient(",
          "  ellipse at 50% 50%,",
          "  rgba(255,255,255,0.2) 0%,",
          "  transparent 70%",
          ")`,  // \u2190 closing backtick on this line",
          "```",
          "",
          "### 3. NO INVENTED HELPER FUNCTIONS",
          "Do NOT call helpers you haven't defined. Use built-ins or write the math inline.",
          "",
          "BAD:",
          "```tsx",
          "const scaled = multiply(value, factor);   // multiply is not defined",
          "const eased = easeOutCubic(t);             // unless you define easeOutCubic",
          "const clamped = clamp(v, 0, 1);            // clamp is not defined",
          "```",
          "",
          "GOOD (use inline math + Math.* / Remotion helpers):",
          "```tsx",
          "const scaled = value * factor;",
          "const eased = interpolate(t, [0, 1], [0, 1], { easing: Easing.out(Easing.cubic) });",
          "const clamped = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, v));",
          "```",
          "",
          "### 4. MUST RETURN JSX WITH AbsoluteFill",
          "The body MUST end with `return (<AbsoluteFill>...</AbsoluteFill>);` \u2014 never just an",
          "object literal, never just a string, never just a `key: value` line. If your scene",
          "has no visible content, still return `<AbsoluteFill style={{ background: '#000' }} />`.",
          "",
          "### 5. NO MASSIVE INLINE ELEMENT ARRAYS",
          "Do NOT generate hundreds/thousands of JSX elements inline. Background patterns",
          "(halftone dots, noise grain, grid cells) that would produce more than ~40 elements",
          "MUST use CSS or SVG `<pattern>` instead of a React `.map()`. Blowing up the DOM",
          "with 1000+ elements freezes the compositor and produces blank frames.",
          "",
          "BAD \u2014 generates 3,600 dots, kills first paint:",
          "```tsx",
          "const halftoneDots = [];",
          "for (let y = 0; y < 1080; y += 24) {",
          "  for (let x = 0; x < 1920; x += 24) {",
          "    halftoneDots.push({ x, y });",
          "  }",
          "}",
          "// ...render: {halftoneDots.map(d => <circle cx={d.x} cy={d.y} r={2} />)}",
          "```",
          "",
          "GOOD \u2014 CSS radial-gradient or SVG pattern, one element:",
          "```tsx",
          "<div style={{",
          "  position: 'absolute', inset: 0, opacity: 0.1,",
          "  backgroundImage: 'radial-gradient(circle, #000 2px, transparent 2px)',",
          "  backgroundSize: '24px 24px'",
          "}} />",
          "```",
          "",
          "Keep decorative arrays (marbles, stars, confetti, particles) at 20 or fewer unless",
          "they're the SCENE'S SUBJECT (a radial-vortex might legitimately have 48 particles)."
        ].join("\n")
      };
