      "",
      "## Music Selection",
      "Pick ONE musicMood from the list above that BEST matches the video's overall vibe.",
      "- Bold/fast narrative \u2192 'hype-launch' or 'saas-teaser'",
      "- Friendly/approachable \u2192 'feel-good-pop' or 'indie-bedroom'",
      "- Edgy/confident \u2192 'phonk-trailer' or 'glitch-hop'",
      "- Cinematic reveal \u2192 'anthem-build' or 'dramatic'",
      "- Catchy/viral \u2192 'tiktok-hook' or 'whistle-hook'",
      "- Chill/minimal \u2192 'lofi-hiphop' or 'minimal'",
      "",
      "## Creative Direction \u2014 TELL A STORY, NOT A FEATURE LIST",
      "",
      "CRITICAL: This video must have a NARRATIVE ARC, not just list features.",
      "",
      "## NEVER REPEAT HEADLINES ACROSS CONSECUTIVE SCENES",
      "",
      "Do NOT emit 2 or 3 scenes in a row with the same (or nearly the same) headline.",
      "If you want a progressive 'beat' or emphasis effect, use ONE scene with a",
      "scene type that supports progression \u2014 `ghost-hook` (reveals words one at a",
      "time), `stacked-hierarchy` (multiple text sizes), `camera-text` (camera moves",
      "through progressive words). Each of these shows multiple text beats WITHIN a",
      "single scene, not across separate scenes.",
      "",
      "BAD:",
      "  Scene 0: 'Hours writing emails.' (120 frames)",
      "  Scene 1: 'Hours writing emails.' (120 frames)  \u2190 duplicate, wastes time",
      "  Scene 2: 'Hours writing emails.' (120 frames)  \u2190 duplicate, wastes time",
      "",
      "GOOD:",
      "  Scene 0: { type: 'ghost-hook', ghostWords: ['Hours', 'writing', 'emails.'], durationFrames: 240 }",
      "  \u2014 same idea, one scene, properly animated word-by-word reveal.",
      "",
      "IMPORTANT: Introduce the PRODUCT NAME by scene 2-3. The viewer needs to know WHO",
      "is talking to them early. Don't wait until scene 5-6 to reveal the brand. Pattern:",
      "  Scene 1-2: Hook (the problem)  \u2192  Scene 2-3: Brand reveal (Meet [Product])  \u2192  Then features/proof",
      "Use `camera-text` for the brand reveal \u2014 it's the premium 'Meet [Product]' moment.",
      "",
      "First, CLASSIFY the company based on the captured data and choose the BEST narrative framework:",
      "",
      "### Framework A: Problem \u2192 Brand \u2192 Proof \u2192 Outcome (general SaaS, productivity tools)",
      "1. HOOK (1-2 scenes): Name the viewer's pain. 'Your tools work against each other.'",
      "2. BRAND REVEAL (1 scene): Introduce the product. 'Meet [Product].' Use camera-text.",
      "3. VALUE (2-3 scenes): Show what the product does. Aspirational, not technical.",
      "4. PROOF (2-3 scenes): Show key capabilities, stats, social proof. Vary visuals.",
      "5. OUTCOME (1 scene): What life looks like after. Confident, clean.",
      "6. CTA (1 scene): Product name + call to action.",
      "",
      "### Framework B: Chaos \u2192 Brand \u2192 Clarity (infrastructure, AI, ops, data platforms)",
      "1. HOOK (1-2 scenes): Show overwhelming complexity. 'Too many tools. Too many tabs.'",
      "2. BRAND REVEAL (1 scene): 'Meet [Product].' The calm after the storm. Use camera-text.",
      "3. CLARITY (2-3 scenes): Show the simplified system. Modular, organized.",
      "4. PROOF (1-2 scenes): Stats, integrations, social proof.",
      "5. OUTCOME (1 scene): Clean, unified result.",
      "6. CTA (1 scene): Product name + call to action.",
      "",
      "### Framework C: Old Way \u2192 Brand \u2192 New Way (disruptive tools, new categories)",
      "1. HOOK (1-2 scenes): 'The old way is broken.' Bold, confrontational.",
      "2. BRAND REVEAL (1 scene): 'Meet [Product]. There's a better way.' Use camera-text.",
